00:17:44.532 --> 00:17:46.768
His parents basically
gave him a vacation home.

254
00:17:46.901 --> 00:17:48.068
Look up.

255
00:17:49.369 --> 00:17:51.138
[jackhammer drilling
in distance]

256
00:17:52.372 --> 00:17:54.274
Since when do you have a gun?

257
00:17:54.408 --> 00:17:57.011
That is not mine.
It's Joseph's.

258
00:17:57.144 --> 00:17:58.412
I think he wants
to be a badass.

259
00:17:58.546 --> 00:18:00.915
-Joseph. badass?
-[laughs]

260
00:18:01.049 --> 00:18:03.450
It's cute. [chuckling]

261
00:18:24.005 --> 00:18:25.339
[Alice sniffling]

262
00:18:30.477 --> 00:18:31.546
[Alice] Hi. Polly.

263
00:18:31.679 --> 00:18:32.479
How are you?

264
00:18:32.614 --> 00:18:33.748
[Susan] She won't remember you.

265
00:18:36.383 --> 00:18:38.251
[Alice] It's only been
a year. though.

266
00:18:41.856 --> 00:18:43.891
[Susan] We must be
the same size.

267
00:18:48.328 --> 00:18:50.163
-[dog whines]
-[gasps]

268
00:18:50.297 --> 00:18:51.498
[speaking French]

269
00:18:54.802 --> 00:18:55.670
[whistles]

270
00:19:03.176 --> 00:19:04.712
[in English] Do you think that
with the construction

271
00:19:04.846 --> 00:19:06.179
-that we could--
-Oh. no. no. Don't worry.

272
00:19:06.313 --> 00:19:07.815
They promised me
they would stop at noon.

273
00:19:07.949 --> 00:19:10.652
and they should be
wrapping up any minute now.

274
00:19:10.785 --> 00:19:13.821
-We're gathered here to--
-[intense drilling]

275
00:19:17.125 --> 00:19:19.994
[raises voice] We're gathered
here today to celebrate

276
00:19:20.128 --> 00:19:22.630
the life of William Price.

277
00:19:22.764 --> 00:19:27.035
to pay tribute and to share
memories of him.

278
00:19:27.167 --> 00:19:29.604
Because for as long as those...

279
00:19:30.170 --> 00:19:31.706
memories live on.

280
00:19:32.573 --> 00:19:34.509
William will always be with us.

281
00:19:35.208 --> 00:19:37.344
I would now like to ask...

282
00:19:37.477 --> 00:19:38.746
[drilling continues]

283
00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:41.281
...Mrs. Susan Price.
William's mother.

284
00:19:41.415 --> 00:19:43.383
to please share a few words.

285
00:19:46.754 --> 00:19:48.388
Bonnie. what are you doing?

286
00:19:48.523 --> 00:19:51.693
No. that's Susan. Grandma.
Aunt Bonnie isn't with us.

287
00:19:51.826 --> 00:19:53.695
[Edgar] Don't waste
your breath on her.

288
00:19:55.262 --> 00:19:56.564
[drilling continues]

289
00:20:11.846 --> 00:20:12.780
William.

290
00:20:14.849 --> 00:20:16.884
my sweet boy.

291
00:20:17.018 --> 00:20:21.254
I could go on for hours about
what an amazing child he was.

292
00:20:22.156 --> 00:20:23.490
a model teenager.

293
00:20:24.324 --> 00:20:28.228
and a man who made us
so. so proud.

294
00:20:28.361 --> 00:20:32.800
He was so enamored
with French cuisine that.
when he studied in Paris.

295
00:20:32.934 --> 00:20:36.971
he surprised us
by bringing home
a French wife. Alice.

296
00:20:41.475 --> 00:20:43.811
Will dreamed
of starting a family.

297
00:20:43.945 --> 00:20:45.513
[intense drilling]

298
00:20:52.587 --> 00:20:54.722
You two would have made
such outstanding parents...

299
00:20:54.856 --> 00:20:58.092
[sniffling] ...and we could
have been Grandpa Edgar

300
00:20:58.226 --> 00:21:00.628
and and Grandma Susan.

301
00:21:00.762 --> 00:21:04.832
I would give anything for us
to be together again.

302
00:21:08.736 --> 00:21:09.937
[crematorium manager]
Thank you. Susan.

303
00:21:10.071 --> 00:21:11.572
And. um... [clears throat]

304
00:21:11.706 --> 00:21:14.609
I'm very sorry about the...
the noise. [clears throat]

305
00:21:16.376 --> 00:21:17.779
[sighs] Alice.

306
00:21:19.147 --> 00:21:21.381
Would you like to share
something with us?

307
00:21:21.516 --> 00:21:23.017
Special memory of your husband?

308
00:21:25.285 --> 00:21:26.954
I... I didn't prepare a speech.

309
00:21:30.992 --> 00:21:31.826
Oh.

310
00:21:32.392 --> 00:21:35.863
Okay. Um. well. uh...

311
00:21:35.997 --> 00:21:41.334
So I would like to play a song
that held a special place

312
00:21:41.468 --> 00:21:43.303
in William's heart.

313
00:21:43.436 --> 00:21:44.605
your wedding song.

314
00:21:44.739 --> 00:21:46.541
[gentle music playing]

315
00:21:51.245 --> 00:21:53.648
[ <i>La Chanson des vieux amants</i>
by Jacques Brel playing]

316
00:22:06.493 --> 00:22:07.995
[music continues]

317
00:22:36.924 --> 00:22:37.792
[music stops]

318
00:22:45.032 --> 00:22:47.400
-[casket creaking]
-[wheels squeaking]

319
00:22:52.640 --> 00:22:53.708
[door slams]

320
00:22:55.343 --> 00:22:56.577
[phone clicking]

321
00:22:56.711 --> 00:22:58.045
[ <i>Hallehova</i>
by Sliim Bambino playing]

322
00:23:00.281 --> 00:23:01.649
[man rapping]

323
00:23:01.782 --> 00:23:03.416
<i>♪ I want the money</i>
<i>I want the car ♪</i>

324
00:23:03.551 --> 00:23:06.020
♪ <i>I want your woman</i>
<i>Be telling me I'm a star</i> ♪

325
00:23:06.153 --> 00:23:08.623
♪ <i>And for the rest of it.</i>
<i>Homie. I pray to God</i> ♪

326
00:23:08.756 --> 00:23:09.957
<i>♪ I'm yelling hova ♪</i>

327
00:23:10.091 --> 00:23:11.726
♪ <i>Halle. halle. hallehova</i> ♪

328
00:23:11.859 --> 00:23:13.861
<i>♪ Hova Halle halle halle ♪</i>

329
00:23:13.995 --> 00:23:16.063
<i>♪ What</i>
<i>What these bitches want ♪</i>

330
00:23:16.197 --> 00:23:18.199
♪ <i>When they spend about a dozen</i>
<i>Summers gettin' real dope</i> ♪

331
00:23:18.332 --> 00:23:19.567
<i>♪ Where they're lookin'</i>
<i>At my Twitter ♪</i>

332
00:23:19.700 --> 00:23:21.302
<i>♪ When I have these lil' hoes ♪</i>

333
00:23:21.434 --> 00:23:23.104
<i>♪ Livin'. spittin' like</i>
<i>They think they real pros ♪</i>

334
00:23:23.237 --> 00:23:24.939
<i>♪ With the quote fingers</i>
<i>Hear me. though ♪</i>

335
00:23:25.072 --> 00:23:26.908
<i>♪ I can smell a fraud</i>
<i>Like a dog do ♪</i>

336
00:23:27.041 --> 00:23:29.476
<i>♪ Talkin' whether it be winter.</i>
<i>Autumn. but they fall through ♪</i>

337
00:23:29.610 --> 00:23:32.213
<i>♪ Sue me if you think</i>
<i>You got it better</i>
<i>With the boss. fool ♪</i>

338
00:23:32.346 --> 00:23:35.049
<i>♪ This is real rap</i>
<i>Motherfucker</i>
<i>This ain't law school ♪</i>

339
00:23:36.117 --> 00:23:37.818
[banging on door]

340
00:23:38.352 --> 00:23:39.419
[buzzes]

341
00:23:43.224 --> 00:23:47.194
I'd like to say goodbye
to my son one last time.

342
00:23:49.163 --> 00:23:50.631
Um. well...

343
00:23:50.765 --> 00:23:53.534
you'll be able to collect
the ashes in a couple of days.

344
00:23:53.668 --> 00:23:55.703
but you're not actually
allowed back here--

345
00:23:55.836 --> 00:23:56.804
Sir!

346
00:23:58.272 --> 00:23:59.640
Sir. my son just died.

347
00:24:03.577 --> 00:24:04.912
Five minutes.

348
00:24:05.046 --> 00:24:06.847
And don't tell anyone
or I'll get yelled at.

349
00:24:06.981 --> 00:24:08.516
Thank you.

350
00:24:08.649 --> 00:24:10.851
My condolences.

351
00:24:12.687 --> 00:24:14.555
[door slams]

352
00:24:36.177 --> 00:24:38.179
[sobs]

353
00:24:43.751 --> 00:24:46.520
-[sobbing]
-[knocking]

354
00:24:56.597 --> 00:24:58.366
[knocking]

355
00:24:58.498 --> 00:25:00.568
[suspenseful music playing]

356
00:25:23.057 --> 00:25:25.026
-[thudding]
-Fuck! [gasps]

357
00:25:25.159 --> 00:25:27.028
Will! Will!

358
00:25:28.262 --> 00:25:30.631
Hang on! Hang-- Hang on!

359
00:25:30.765 --> 00:25:33.467
Oh! Will! I'm coming!

360
00:25:33.601 --> 00:25:35.669
Will! Hold on. son!

361
00:25:36.170 --> 00:25:37.171
[grunting]

362
00:25:39.140 --> 00:25:40.775
I'm coming! Fuck.

363
00:25:41.375 --> 00:25:42.810
[straining]

364
00:25:44.111 --> 00:25:45.679
[yells]

365
00:25:45.813 --> 00:25:48.149
-[groans]
-[objects shattering]

366
00:25:49.483 --> 00:25:50.684
[groaning]

367
00:25:51.886 --> 00:25:53.921
[creature growling]

368
00:25:55.489 --> 00:25:56.690
[whimpering]

369
00:25:58.793 --> 00:26:00.795
What the fuck?

370
00:26:02.596 --> 00:26:04.331
[man screams]

371
00:26:04.465 --> 00:26:06.200
[agonized screams continue]

372
00:26:06.333 --> 00:26:08.702
Help! Help!

373
00:26:11.672 --> 00:26:13.841
[sinister music playing]

374
00:26:29.657 --> 00:26:32.561
[car horn blaring]

375
00:26:32.693 --> 00:26:33.861
-Come with us.
-Okay.

376
00:26:33.994 --> 00:26:34.829
-Okay. We'll see you there.
-Okay.

377
00:26:34.962 --> 00:26:37.798
[horn continues blaring]

378
00:26:42.069 --> 00:26:43.804
[Alice] How far is it? Damn.

379
00:26:43.938 --> 00:26:45.706
[Thya]
Less than five minutes away.

380
00:26:45.840 --> 00:26:46.941
[Alice] Oh. fucking--

381
00:26:47.074 --> 00:26:48.476
You okay?

382
00:26:48.609 --> 00:26:49.944
Yeah. no. it's just--

383
00:26:50.077 --> 00:26:51.779
you know
they don't want me there.

384
00:26:52.547 --> 00:26:53.848
That's not true.

385
00:26:54.348 --> 00:26:55.616
Kit. in here.

386
00:26:57.051 --> 00:26:58.953
-Jesus.
-[Thya laughs]

387
00:26:59.086 --> 00:27:01.455
All right. look.
The only thing they care about
is that we're all together.

388
00:27:01.590 --> 00:27:03.023
You're part of the family.

389
00:27:03.157 --> 00:27:05.092
Even my mom. She said
that she was really touched

390
00:27:05.226 --> 00:27:08.229
you agreed to the cremation
instead of the burial.

391
00:27:08.362 --> 00:27:10.464
And we could do it
where she wanted.

392
00:27:10.599 --> 00:27:11.799
[chuckles]

393
00:27:11.932 --> 00:27:13.434
She appreciates you. Honestly.

394
00:27:13.568 --> 00:27:15.369
Yeah. maybe. I don't know.

395
00:27:16.370 --> 00:27:17.771
Well. I mean. my dad.
on the other hand.

396
00:27:17.905 --> 00:27:19.140
I mean.
he can't fucking stand you.

397
00:27:19.273 --> 00:27:21.510
Oh. God. [laughs]

398
00:27:21.642 --> 00:27:23.844
[ethereal music playing]

399
00:27:39.894 --> 00:27:41.695
[Alice] Looks so run-down now.

400
00:27:41.829 --> 00:27:43.931
[Thya]
Wait. you've been here before?

401
00:27:44.064 --> 00:27:45.866
[Alice] We got married here.

402
00:27:58.412 --> 00:27:59.780
Mom? Dad?

403
00:28:01.916 --> 00:28:03.250
Be right back.

404
00:28:10.291 --> 00:28:12.293
Grandma. You know where Mom is?

405
00:28:12.426 --> 00:28:16.764
Oh. She's still at school.
It lets out at 4:00.

406
00:28:17.364 --> 00:28:18.899
Yeah. Thank you.

407
00:28:29.843 --> 00:28:31.045
Mom?

408
00:28:38.786 --> 00:28:40.354
[bed frame creaking]

409
00:28:40.487 --> 00:28:41.690
What are you doing?

410
00:28:41.822 --> 00:28:45.292
What do you think?
You invited Alice.

411
00:28:45.426 --> 00:28:46.860
She was Will's wife.

412
00:28:48.028 --> 00:28:50.030
Here. Mom. let me do this.

413
00:28:52.233 --> 00:28:53.367
When we gave you this place.

414
00:28:53.500 --> 00:28:55.035
I asked you to throw
everything away.

415
00:28:55.169 --> 00:28:57.304
Why are his things still here?

416
00:28:57.438 --> 00:29:00.908
I just wanted to keep
something from Grandpa.

417
00:29:01.041 --> 00:29:02.343
It felt like
I was throwing him away.

418
00:29:02.476 --> 00:29:03.545
He threw us away.

419
00:29:03.678 --> 00:29:05.212
[Joseph]
No. I know. It's just--

420
00:29:05.346 --> 00:29:08.015
I mean. some of this stuff.
it's fascinating. you know?

421
00:29:08.148 --> 00:29:10.184
[Benjamin] <i>Unleashing</i>
<i>flesh-possessing demons</i>

422
00:29:10.317 --> 00:29:14.822
<i>so malevolent as though</i>
<i>the devil himself were here.</i>

423
00:29:14.955 --> 00:29:17.091
Does that sound fascinating
to you?

424
00:29:17.224 --> 00:29:19.628
It's just inspiration
for my book.

425
00:29:19.760 --> 00:29:21.730
Your book is about Grandpa?

426
00:29:21.862 --> 00:29:23.264
No. not him.

427
00:29:23.397 --> 00:29:25.533
His research.
I mean-- [chuckles]

428
00:29:25.667 --> 00:29:28.670
Come on. Curses. and demons.

429
00:29:28.802 --> 00:29:30.404
I found all kinds
of crazy artifacts

430
00:29:30.538 --> 00:29:32.172
he brought back
from around the world

431
00:29:32.306 --> 00:29:35.109
and apparently. he was
part of some secret society.

432
00:29:35.809 --> 00:29:37.244
It was a cult.

433
00:29:37.378 --> 00:29:39.213
[Joseph] They were historians.
you know.

434
00:29:39.346 --> 00:29:41.382
And he recorded everything
in his notebook.

435
00:29:42.116 --> 00:29:44.051
Look. I was gonna tell you.

436
00:29:44.184 --> 00:29:45.986
[Susan] No. let me tell you.

437
00:29:46.120 --> 00:29:48.188
My father was not a good man.
Joseph.

438
00:29:48.322 --> 00:29:49.490
Mom--

439
00:29:49.624 --> 00:29:53.427
When my mom's mind
started to go. he retreated.

440
00:29:53.561 --> 00:29:56.263
Spent more time
with the Circle of the Wise Men
than us.

441
00:29:56.397 --> 00:29:59.300
Always off on some expedition.

442
00:29:59.433 --> 00:30:01.802
buried in some stupid old book.

443
00:30:01.935 --> 00:30:03.705
When Aunt Bonnie got sick.

444
00:30:03.837 --> 00:30:05.272
that's when he left us
for good.

445
00:30:05.406 --> 00:30:08.442
Hunting for rusty weapons.
Crumbling scrolls.

446
00:30:08.576 --> 00:30:10.978
He said he had to find a way
to protect us from evil.

447
00:30:11.111 --> 00:30:12.279
All he ever did
was talk like that

448
00:30:12.413 --> 00:30:13.914
because
he didn't have the courage

449
00:30:14.048 --> 00:30:15.916
to face real hardship.

450
00:30:16.050 --> 00:30:17.217
[inhales sharply]

451
00:30:17.351 --> 00:30:19.820
I had to take care
of this family.

452
00:30:20.689 --> 00:30:21.922
I'm sorry. Mom.

453
00:30:22.056 --> 00:30:23.857
[dog barks distantly]

454
00:30:33.133 --> 00:30:34.435
-You should get some rest.
-It's fine.

455
00:30:34.569 --> 00:30:36.604
I'm fine. It's the pills.

456
00:30:38.172 --> 00:30:40.240
Tell everyone lunch in an hour.

457
00:30:40.374 --> 00:30:41.543
[sighs]

458
00:30:44.111 --> 00:30:45.379
Throw this out.

459
00:30:47.214 --> 00:30:48.282
[Polly wailing]

460
00:30:48.415 --> 00:30:49.883
-Let go of me!
-What's going on?

461
00:30:50.017 --> 00:30:51.720
She insists on going outside
by herself.

462
00:30:51.852 --> 00:30:53.320
[Polly wails] No! No!

463
00:30:53.454 --> 00:30:55.022
[groans] <i>Putain.</i> Polly!

464
00:30:55.155 --> 00:30:56.156
-[Joseph] Grandma!
-I was just trying to help!

465
00:30:56.290 --> 00:30:57.625
-No. no. no.
-Bonnie! Bonnie!

466
00:30:57.759 --> 00:30:59.927
I've got her. She's trying
to steal my money.

467
00:31:00.060 --> 00:31:01.228
Call the police!

468
00:31:01.362 --> 00:31:02.764
-Susan. we were just trying--
-Bonnie!

469
00:31:02.896 --> 00:31:05.032
-[Joseph] Grandma. you okay?
-[Susan] Calm down.

470
00:31:05.165 --> 00:31:07.901
-It's broken.
-Just a sec. Mom.

471
00:31:09.571 --> 00:31:11.506
[chair beeping]

472
00:31:15.677 --> 00:31:16.977
You thief.

473
00:31:17.779 --> 00:31:19.514
Oh. my God.

474
00:31:19.647 --> 00:31:22.383
[man coughing]

475
00:31:25.052 --> 00:31:26.253
Dad?

476
00:31:28.757 --> 00:31:31.091
[coughing continues]

477
00:31:31.992 --> 00:31:34.662
-Dad.
-[ignition fails]

478
00:31:34.796 --> 00:31:36.397
[sniffs]

479
00:31:36.531 --> 00:31:37.898
[ignition fails]

480
00:31:38.031 --> 00:31:38.966
It's out of gas.

481
00:31:39.099 --> 00:31:40.467
[clattering]

482
00:31:43.638 --> 00:31:45.105
You don't need to worry
about the yard.

483
00:31:45.239 --> 00:31:46.940
[Edgar] Someone's gotta do it.

484
00:31:47.074 --> 00:31:50.712
-I will. I just haven't had--
-We leave you this house...

485
00:31:50.845 --> 00:31:52.312
And you let it rot.

486
00:31:53.347 --> 00:31:55.215
You like living in shit!

487
00:31:56.818 --> 00:31:58.385
[coughs. grunts]

488
00:32:04.893 --> 00:32:07.060
[stairs creaking]

489
00:32:10.998 --> 00:32:13.066
[coughs]

490
00:32:13.200 --> 00:32:16.437
[coughs repeatedly]

491
00:32:16.571 --> 00:32:18.540
-[heavy thud]
-[objects clattering]

492
00:32:22.677 --> 00:32:23.678
[Will] Dad.

493
00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:28.949
Dad. Help me.

494
00:32:49.069 --> 00:32:50.572
[glass shattering]

495
00:32:52.272 --> 00:32:53.608
[Will] We're inside.

496
00:32:53.741 --> 00:32:54.742
[ominous music playing]

497
00:32:54.876 --> 00:32:57.411
[demonic voices whispering]

498
00:33:00.280 --> 00:33:01.683
-[Will] <i>Let us in. Dad.</i>
-[grunts]

499
00:33:03.918 --> 00:33:05.486
<i>It's okay.</i>

500
00:33:05.620 --> 00:33:08.355
-[female demonic voice] <i>Do it!</i>
-[Will] <i>Don't fight.</i>

501
00:33:10.224 --> 00:33:12.292
[female demonic voice]
<i>Come on. you can do it.</i>

502
00:33:12.993 --> 00:33:14.061
<i>Do it. Do it!</i>

503
00:33:14.194 --> 00:33:15.630
<i>Do it. Do it!</i>

504
00:33:21.034 --> 00:33:22.469
[Alice] Edgar?

505
00:33:24.973 --> 00:33:26.240
Edgar. are you okay?

506
00:33:29.209 --> 00:33:30.344
[objects clattering]

507
00:33:30.477 --> 00:33:32.714
[Alice strains. grunts]

508
00:33:33.781 --> 00:33:35.382
[grunts]

509
00:33:36.216 --> 00:33:38.385
[Alice breathes heavily]

510
00:33:41.890 --> 00:33:43.123
[grunts]

511
00:33:47.027 --> 00:33:48.462
Don't tell my wife.

512
00:33:49.062 --> 00:33:50.230
Please.

513
00:33:50.865 --> 00:33:52.600
I'll hold onto this. okay?

514
00:33:53.467 --> 00:33:54.334
Mm.

515
00:34:01.241 --> 00:34:03.545
[vegetables rattling]

516
00:34:04.946 --> 00:34:06.380
[winding timer]

517
00:34:17.725 --> 00:34:18.526
What happened?

518
00:34:18.660 --> 00:34:20.360
I missed a step in the cellar.

519
00:34:20.494 --> 00:34:22.062
I dropped the plates.
I'm sorry.

520
00:34:22.195 --> 00:34:24.498
[Susan] Yes. I heard that.

521
00:34:24.632 --> 00:34:26.701
Would you put this
on the dining room table?

522
00:34:26.834 --> 00:34:28.168
Please be careful with it.

523
00:34:28.770 --> 00:34:30.103
Made it myself.

524
00:34:30.237 --> 00:34:31.238
You did?

525
00:34:31.371 --> 00:34:32.406
It's Niobe.

526
00:34:32.540 --> 00:34:34.042
-A Greek queen.
-[exhales]

527
00:34:34.174 --> 00:34:36.410
-She's Edgar's favorite.
-It's pretty.

528
00:34:37.011 --> 00:34:38.211
Yeah.

529
00:34:39.013 --> 00:34:40.347
Why did you stop?

530
00:34:40.480 --> 00:34:42.316
[smacks lips] First. the kids.

531
00:34:42.449 --> 00:34:44.318
Then my sister Bonnie got sick.

532
00:34:44.451 --> 00:34:46.554
And my mother
couldn't live on her own.

533
00:34:47.021 --> 00:34:48.221
Well...

534
00:34:49.222 --> 00:34:51.158
You had a gift. It's a shame.

535
00:34:51.291 --> 00:34:52.694
Why is it a shame?

536
00:34:53.393 --> 00:34:55.863
I was with the people I love.

537
00:34:55.997 --> 00:34:57.565
Building a life.

538
00:34:57.699 --> 00:35:01.869
You know. without my family.
I'm nothing.

539
00:35:03.905 --> 00:35:05.439
[indistinct chatter]

540
00:35:06.406 --> 00:35:08.776
[sound distortion on tape]

541
00:35:09.276 --> 00:35:11.244
[laughter]

542
00:35:14.716 --> 00:35:17.217
[dog whines]

543
00:35:26.493 --> 00:35:28.428
Thank you. Joseph.

544
00:35:28.563 --> 00:35:30.665
That was beautiful.

545
00:35:30.798 --> 00:35:32.533
[Edgar coughs]

546
00:35:34.569 --> 00:35:36.804
-You okay?
-Mm.

547
00:35:36.938 --> 00:35:37.805
I'm good.

548
00:35:45.079 --> 00:35:46.313
No.

549
00:35:47.347 --> 00:35:48.583
That's Will's seat.

550
00:35:48.716 --> 00:35:51.753
[Polly] Oh. My big boy. Will.

551
00:35:51.886 --> 00:35:53.554
When does he get here?

552
00:35:54.421 --> 00:35:56.658
-[heavy thud]
-[objects clattering]

553
00:36:04.398 --> 00:36:07.367
Edgar.
Would you do the wine. please?

554
00:36:10.938 --> 00:36:13.173
Oh. don't worry. I got it.

555
00:36:17.444 --> 00:36:19.312
[Joseph] Mmm. So good.

556
00:36:20.247 --> 00:36:22.817
They're premade.
I just heated them.

557
00:36:22.950 --> 00:36:25.787
Joseph is right. they're--
they're delicious.

558
00:36:25.920 --> 00:36:27.922
I would never guess
it was frozen.

559
00:36:28.823 --> 00:36:30.357
That's concerning.

560
00:36:32.126 --> 00:36:33.260
Hmm?

561
00:36:33.393 --> 00:36:36.463
It's clearly frozen food
on paper plates.

562
00:36:36.597 --> 00:36:38.465
If you manage
the restaurant alone.

563
00:36:38.599 --> 00:36:40.568
you'll need to know frozen
from fresh.

564
00:36:46.306 --> 00:36:48.109
About the restaurant. I'm--

565
00:36:48.241 --> 00:36:50.712
I'm not sure I plan to--

566
00:36:51.612 --> 00:36:53.848
Let's just talk about it
another time.

567
00:36:53.981 --> 00:36:55.616
Let's talk about it now.

568
00:36:56.084 --> 00:36:57.618
We're all here.

569
00:36:57.752 --> 00:36:59.954
Well. I haven't decided
anything.

570
00:37:00.088 --> 00:37:02.190
but I mean.
it was Will's restaurant--

571
00:37:02.322 --> 00:37:03.423
You ran the place together.

572
00:37:03.558 --> 00:37:04.959
I only did the accounting.

573
00:37:05.093 --> 00:37:08.295
But you're his wife.

574
00:37:13.868 --> 00:37:15.235
You sure?

575
00:37:17.739 --> 00:37:19.473
[Alice]
To be honest. I was thinking

576
00:37:19.607 --> 00:37:21.843
I might go back to Paris
for a while.

577
00:37:22.910 --> 00:37:25.546
Maybe stay with my--
with my dad.

578
00:37:25.680 --> 00:37:29.282
Then things seem a little more
decided than you let on.

579
00:37:29.416 --> 00:37:30.785
No. no. no. I just thought--

580
00:37:30.918 --> 00:37:32.285
These things should be
dealt with as a family.

581
00:37:32.419 --> 00:37:33.755
Yeah.

582
00:37:33.888 --> 00:37:36.057
We should deal with it
as a family.

583
00:37:37.024 --> 00:37:39.026
[Susan]
You know the staff adores you.

584
00:37:39.160 --> 00:37:42.395
Alice. they need you.

585
00:37:42.530 --> 00:37:45.332
Think about Will.
Do it for him.

586
00:37:46.433 --> 00:37:48.970
Wait. I recognize you.

587
00:37:49.103 --> 00:37:52.039
You're married to my grandson.
aren't you?

588
00:37:53.841 --> 00:37:56.476
Don't turn a deaf ear.
I asked you a question.

589
00:37:56.611 --> 00:37:58.411
-It's all right. Shh.
-I--

590
00:37:58.546 --> 00:38:00.081
It's okay. It's okay.

591
00:38:00.214 --> 00:38:02.183
All I'm saying is...

592
00:38:02.315 --> 00:38:05.186
you have the chance to take
over a successful business

593
00:38:05.318 --> 00:38:07.555
while honoring Will
at the same time.

594
00:38:08.156 --> 00:38:09.590
It was his life's work.

595
00:38:09.724 --> 00:38:11.959
It was his passion.

596
00:38:12.093 --> 00:38:13.661
And you should carry it on.

597
00:38:13.795 --> 00:38:16.230
Susan. I really think
we should do this
another time.

598
00:38:16.363 --> 00:38:19.332
No. now's the best time to lay
everything on the table.

599
00:38:19.466 --> 00:38:21.769
[Susan] He's right.
We need to make
decisions together.

600
00:38:21.903 --> 00:38:23.436
You are driving me
fucking crazy!

601
00:38:23.571 --> 00:38:24.839
<i>Without me.</i>
<i>you are nothing. Alice.</i>

602
00:38:24.972 --> 00:38:26.174
It's what Will
would have wanted.

603
00:38:26.306 --> 00:38:27.842
[Edgar] <i>That's Will's seat.</i>

604
00:38:27.975 --> 00:38:29.442
-That's your fucking problem!
-[Susan] <i>Do it for him.</i>

605
00:38:29.577 --> 00:38:31.344
[Polly]
<i>Will. When does he get here?</i>

606
00:38:31.478 --> 00:38:32.947
We're trying to have
a fucking kid!

607
00:38:33.080 --> 00:38:35.817
You do not know
what you fucking want!

608
00:38:35.950 --> 00:38:38.853
Say it. Don't you fucking
bait me. Alice.

609
00:38:40.955 --> 00:38:41.889
Alice!

610
00:38:42.023 --> 00:38:43.724
Please. calm down.

611
00:38:45.159 --> 00:38:46.928
I am calm.

612
00:38:47.061 --> 00:38:49.429
But you shouldn't speak
on Will's behalf.

613
00:38:50.363 --> 00:38:51.532
[Susan] I'm his mother.

614
00:38:51.666 --> 00:38:54.035
No one knows him
better than I do.

615
00:38:54.168 --> 00:38:55.903
[Polly slurping]

616
00:38:56.037 --> 00:38:57.071
Grandma. no.

617
00:38:58.639 --> 00:39:00.107
Sorry. Okay. look.

618
00:39:00.241 --> 00:39:02.710
we're all here for him.
but I think Alice is right.

619
00:39:02.844 --> 00:39:04.078
This isn't the right time to--

620
00:39:04.212 --> 00:39:06.647
It's never the right time
for you. is it?

621
00:39:08.783 --> 00:39:10.518
That's why you've done nothing
with your life.

622
00:39:10.651 --> 00:39:12.019
[Susan] Edgar. Please.

623
00:39:12.153 --> 00:39:13.353
Don't you fucking touch me.

624
00:39:13.486 --> 00:39:14.622
[Thya]
Edgar. we're all grieving here

625
00:39:14.755 --> 00:39:16.624
but that's no reason
to be cruel. I--

626
00:39:16.757 --> 00:39:18.425
-It's fine.
-It's not.

627
00:39:18.559 --> 00:39:20.528
-Joe--
-Where is it?

628
00:39:22.663 --> 00:39:24.832
Where's the wedding ring?

629
00:39:25.600 --> 00:39:26.801
Why aren't you wearing it?

630
00:39:26.934 --> 00:39:30.071
Did you sell it?
You get a good price?

631
00:39:30.204 --> 00:39:32.039
No! No. no. of course not. I--

632
00:39:32.173 --> 00:39:34.407
Edgar. can I have
the corkscrew. please?

633
00:39:35.910 --> 00:39:38.411
[Edgar]
And a hoodie and sneakers

634
00:39:38.546 --> 00:39:40.014
at her husband's funeral.

635
00:39:40.147 --> 00:39:42.350
I'm right here. Edgar.
You can speak to me directly.

636
00:39:42.482 --> 00:39:43.885
You didn't even cry.

637
00:39:44.018 --> 00:39:45.418
[dog whining]

638
00:39:45.553 --> 00:39:47.221
Don't you think that's weird?

639
00:39:47.355 --> 00:39:49.790
-People grieve in different--
-Get away from me!

640
00:39:50.390 --> 00:39:51.759
[dog whines]

641
00:40:04.772 --> 00:40:07.440
[Edgar eats noisily]

642
00:40:10.544 --> 00:40:11.846
Will's dead.

643
00:40:11.979 --> 00:40:14.015
And now you inflict this on us?

644
00:40:15.249 --> 00:40:16.784
That's enough.

645
00:40:16.918 --> 00:40:20.688
-Dad. You don't look good--
-It's your fault he's dead.

646
00:40:20.821 --> 00:40:22.823
You didn't stop him
getting to the car!

647
00:40:22.957 --> 00:40:24.525
Stop it. Dad.
I had nothing to do with it.

648
00:40:24.659 --> 00:40:25.826
Will got into a fight
with Alice. and he--

649
00:40:25.960 --> 00:40:28.362
What? Are you implying
it was my fault?

650
00:40:28.495 --> 00:40:29.964
-No. no. of course not.
-You were there.

651
00:40:30.097 --> 00:40:31.498
You couldn't stop him from
getting in the car either.

652
00:40:31.632 --> 00:40:32.733
[Joseph] I know. Alice.
I know. I tried.

653
00:40:32.867 --> 00:40:34.402
[Alice] We tried.
Okay. I didn't.

654
00:40:34.535 --> 00:40:36.003
-Doesn't mean it's my fault.
-That's not what I'm saying.

655
00:40:36.137 --> 00:40:37.371
-It's exactly what you said.
-Alice. no.

656
00:40:37.505 --> 00:40:38.873
-Alice. I think--
-[Alice] No.

657
00:40:39.006 --> 00:40:40.007
I think you should all
mind your own business.

658
00:40:40.141 --> 00:40:40.508
You don't know anything.

659
00:40:41.509 --> 00:40:43.110
You're glad he's dead.

660
00:40:43.244 --> 00:40:46.213
Please. please. please. Will's
looking down on us from above.

661
00:40:47.982 --> 00:40:49.016
From above?

662
00:40:53.354 --> 00:40:55.923
He's down below.

663
00:40:56.057 --> 00:40:57.058
[dog whining]

664
00:40:57.191 --> 00:41:00.094
-[Edgar yells]
-[dog whines in pain]

665
00:41:01.195 --> 00:41:03.364
Dad. what are you doing?
Stop it right now!

666
00:41:03.496 --> 00:41:04.665
-Stop!
-[Thya] No!

667
00:41:04.799 --> 00:41:06.233
[Susan screams]

668
00:41:08.102 --> 00:41:09.503
[Joseph] The dog!

669
00:41:10.104 --> 00:41:11.105
[Edgar] Help me.

670
00:41:12.173 --> 00:41:13.207
Help me.

671
00:41:13.341 --> 00:41:14.308
Help me!

672
00:41:14.442 --> 00:41:16.377
-Get your keys.
-Okay.

673
00:41:16.510 --> 00:41:17.778
[Susan]
Take him to the hospital.

674
00:41:18.946 --> 00:41:20.915
[Joseph] Thya! I need help.
Grab his arm.

675
00:41:21.048 --> 00:41:22.783
-[Thya] I got him. I got him.
-[Joseph] Be careful.

676
00:41:22.917 --> 00:41:25.119
What did we do to deserve this?

677
00:41:25.252 --> 00:41:26.787
[door slams]

678
00:41:26.921 --> 00:41:29.623
They left without
saying goodbye.

679
00:41:34.996 --> 00:41:36.998
Jesus fucking Christ.
is he fucking crazy?

680
00:41:37.131 --> 00:41:38.466
Thya. please. Give me a second.

681
00:41:38.599 --> 00:41:40.801
-He killed your fucking dog!
-I know!

682
00:41:42.203 --> 00:41:45.206
Shit. shit. He's fucking
bleeding everywhere. Shit.

683
00:41:46.874 --> 00:41:49.543
Shit. shit. Come on!

684
00:41:49.677 --> 00:41:51.779
[Joseph breathes heavily]

685
00:41:53.948 --> 00:41:55.383
-Joe?
-What?

686
00:41:55.516 --> 00:41:56.784
Your dad.

687
00:41:58.452 --> 00:42:00.654
[suspenseful music playing]

688
00:42:09.663 --> 00:42:10.965
-[Edgar yells]
-[screams]

689
00:42:11.098 --> 00:42:12.566
No! No!

690
00:42:12.700 --> 00:42:14.668
[screaming. grunting]

691
00:42:26.680 --> 00:42:27.882
[Edgar grunting]

692
00:42:34.355 --> 00:42:35.956
[Joseph straining]

693
00:42:37.558 --> 00:42:39.593
[Edgar yelling]

694
00:42:41.862 --> 00:42:43.798
[Joseph cries in pain]

695
00:42:47.635 --> 00:42:50.104
[Thya screams]

696
00:42:53.274 --> 00:42:54.175
Oh. my fucking God!

697
00:42:56.210 --> 00:42:58.245
-[Edgar growls]
-[Joseph chokes]

698
00:43:00.581 --> 00:43:01.715
[Edgar growls]

699
00:43:02.216 --> 00:43:02.983
[yelling]

700
00:43:03.117 --> 00:43:04.652
[Joseph yelling]

701
00:43:11.292 --> 00:43:12.593
[Joseph] Stop!

702
00:43:13.528 --> 00:43:14.728
[Thya choking]

703
00:43:14.862 --> 00:43:16.063
Let her go!

704
00:43:17.331 --> 00:43:19.400
-[Thya screams]
-I said let her go!

705
00:43:19.534 --> 00:43:20.535
Fucking shoot him!

706
00:43:20.668 --> 00:43:22.269
[Thya choking]

707
00:43:22.403 --> 00:43:24.905
Fucking shoot him! Joe!

708
00:43:25.039 --> 00:43:25.639
[choking]

709
00:43:25.773 --> 00:43:27.408
[Thya choking]

710
00:43:27.542 --> 00:43:29.810
[Edgar] Shoot me. Joe.

711
00:43:31.045 --> 00:43:32.379
Shoot me.

712
00:43:33.314 --> 00:43:35.182
Shoot me.

713
00:43:35.316 --> 00:43:36.317
Shoot me. Joe!

714
00:43:36.450 --> 00:43:37.451
Shoot me!

715
00:43:37.586 --> 00:43:39.854
[all yelling]

716
00:43:44.792 --> 00:43:47.061
[Edgar grunting]

717
00:43:52.700 --> 00:43:54.135
[Edgar snarling]

718
00:43:54.935 --> 00:43:57.771
[Thya screams. gasps]

719
00:43:57.905 --> 00:43:59.874
[hyperventilating]

720
00:44:00.609 --> 00:44:02.276
Joseph!

721
00:44:03.744 --> 00:44:05.846
[Thya gasping]

722
00:44:09.116 --> 00:44:11.218
[Thya screams. gasps]

723
00:44:14.722 --> 00:44:15.990
[gasps]

724
00:44:16.123 --> 00:44:18.159
[demonic music playing]

725
00:44:18.292 --> 00:44:19.827
[inaudible]

726
00:45:12.746 --> 00:45:14.248
[sighs]

727
00:45:22.524 --> 00:45:24.191
[clattering]

728
00:45:25.359 --> 00:45:26.827
[exhales]

729
00:45:59.360 --> 00:46:00.961
"October. 1983.

730
00:46:01.095 --> 00:46:03.130
That cursed <i>Book of the Dead.</i>

731
00:46:03.264 --> 00:46:05.165
I warned them
against reading from it.

732
00:46:05.299 --> 00:46:07.368
The forbidden incantation.

733
00:46:07.501 --> 00:46:10.739
Four words
that can unleash evil.

734
00:46:10.871 --> 00:46:12.973
But they didn't listen.

735
00:46:15.409 --> 00:46:17.111
December. 1983.

736
00:46:17.244 --> 00:46:18.946
At last. I have found it.

737
00:46:19.079 --> 00:46:22.049
A weapon
that can stop them all.

738
00:46:22.182 --> 00:46:27.154
A dagger created
by the Circle of the Wise Men.

739
00:46:27.288 --> 00:46:29.223
<i>The tiniest cut</i>
<i>from this ancient blade</i>

740
00:46:29.356 --> 00:46:31.358
<i>rips their demonic souls</i>
<i>from their bodies.</i>

741
00:46:31.492 --> 00:46:34.228
<i>I've hidden it.</i>
<i>but now must leave again.</i>

742
00:46:34.361 --> 00:46:36.497
<i>These creatures are hunting me</i>

743
00:46:36.631 --> 00:46:40.968
<i>and I must protect</i>
<i>my wife and daughters."</i>

744
00:46:46.574 --> 00:46:48.208
[exhales]

745
00:46:56.850 --> 00:46:59.053
[demonic voices whispering]

746
00:47:02.524 --> 00:47:03.457
"Kunda."

747
00:47:03.591 --> 00:47:05.359
[low growl]

748
00:47:13.867 --> 00:47:14.803
"Astratta."

749
00:47:14.935 --> 00:47:16.937
[low growl]

750
00:47:23.977 --> 00:47:26.180
[demonic voices whispering]

751
00:47:26.880 --> 00:47:27.816
"Montosse."

752
00:47:27.948 --> 00:47:29.983
[low growl]

753
00:47:39.493 --> 00:47:40.427
No. fuck this.

754
00:47:40.562 --> 00:47:41.962
[growling. snarling]

755
00:47:42.096 --> 00:47:44.198
[Alice screams]

756
00:47:46.867 --> 00:47:49.504
-[barking]
-[Alice screams]

757
00:47:53.273 --> 00:47:54.576
-[grunts]
-[knife slices]

758
00:48:19.433 --> 00:48:20.434
Alice?

759
00:48:21.935 --> 00:48:24.271
[exhales] What's wrong?

760
00:48:25.005 --> 00:48:27.007
[in French]

761
00:48:28.342 --> 00:48:30.144
[in English]
I don't understand you.

762
00:48:31.245 --> 00:48:33.447
[Joseph hyperventilating]

763
00:48:34.314 --> 00:48:35.949
[Susan] What happened?

764
00:48:39.052 --> 00:48:40.588
Where's your father?

765
00:48:41.355 --> 00:48:43.957
I think Dad just killed Thya.

766
00:48:44.793 --> 00:48:46.260
[knock at door]

767
00:48:48.128 --> 00:48:50.998
[knocking]

768
00:48:51.131 --> 00:48:53.701
[Thya] Open up. It's me.

769
00:48:56.504 --> 00:48:58.706
She came back for my money.

770
00:48:58.840 --> 00:49:00.974
[breath trembling]

771
00:49:07.549 --> 00:49:10.117
[Thya gurgling]

772
00:49:10.250 --> 00:49:12.219
[demonic music playing]

773
00:49:21.228 --> 00:49:23.397
-[breath trembling]
-[door closes]

774
00:49:28.469 --> 00:49:30.705
[demonic music playing]

775
00:49:37.612 --> 00:49:39.547
[breath trembling]

776
00:49:49.289 --> 00:49:52.192
[bones clicking]

777
00:50:10.410 --> 00:50:13.413
[in demonic voice]
To your perfect family.

778
00:50:15.817 --> 00:50:17.184
Cheers.

779
00:50:19.921 --> 00:50:21.623
[sizzling]

780
00:50:29.162 --> 00:50:30.665
[Thya spits]

781
00:50:33.635 --> 00:50:35.435
[yells]

782
00:50:40.808 --> 00:50:43.076
[grunting. yelling]

783
00:50:52.352 --> 00:50:53.588
[Joseph] No!

784
00:50:55.088 --> 00:50:57.592
-[bone cracks]
-[Thya grunts]

785
00:50:57.725 --> 00:51:00.394
[panting]

786
00:51:00.528 --> 00:51:02.262
[in normal voice]
Joe. it hurts.

787
00:51:02.396 --> 00:51:04.599
-Please. Joe.
-Joe. no!

788
00:51:05.232 --> 00:51:06.734
[door slams]

789
00:51:06.868 --> 00:51:08.036
[muffled sobbing]

790
00:51:08.168 --> 00:51:09.504
[Susan] Where is your father?

791
00:51:09.637 --> 00:51:12.239
We gotta go. We gotta go.
Alice! Alice. come on!

792
00:51:13.508 --> 00:51:14.909
Come on. we gotta go!

793
00:51:15.043 --> 00:51:17.177
[ominous music playing]

794
00:51:26.821 --> 00:51:28.221
Edgar.

795
00:51:29.389 --> 00:51:30.725
-Sweetheart.
-Susan. don't.

796
00:51:30.858 --> 00:51:32.125
-Get off me!
-Mom!

797
00:51:32.259 --> 00:51:34.696
[breath trembling]

798
00:51:38.165 --> 00:51:39.366
[whistles]

799
00:51:43.203 --> 00:51:45.573
[whimpering]

800
00:51:51.178 --> 00:51:53.246
[Susan gasps]

801
00:51:56.551 --> 00:51:58.753
[in demonic voice]
You should be dead.

802
00:51:58.886 --> 00:52:00.822
Not Will.

803
00:52:00.955 --> 00:52:02.255
[breath trembling]

804
00:52:05.425 --> 00:52:06.694
-No!
-[screams]

805
00:52:27.347 --> 00:52:28.750
[moans]

806
00:52:51.238 --> 00:52:53.007
[ominous music playing]

807
00:52:53.141 --> 00:52:54.876
[sizzling]

808
00:53:00.414 --> 00:53:02.884
[whooshes. crackling]

809
00:53:03.651 --> 00:53:04.952
[hissing]

810
00:53:05.086 --> 00:53:06.688
[whistling]

811
00:53:10.124 --> 00:53:11.926
[suspenseful music playing]

812
00:53:17.464 --> 00:53:19.433
[Joseph panting]

813
00:53:26.473 --> 00:53:28.442
[hissing. whistling]

814
00:53:28.576 --> 00:53:30.277
[both breathing heavily]

815
00:53:37.885 --> 00:53:39.486
[breathing heavily]

816
00:53:58.005 --> 00:53:59.774
[breath trembling]

817
00:54:02.844 --> 00:54:05.345
He's just standing there.
staring.

818
00:54:05.479 --> 00:54:07.181
We're fucking trapped!

819
00:54:07.314 --> 00:54:08.482
[Susan] I'll be
right back. Mom.

820
00:54:19.292 --> 00:54:20.360
[thuds on door]

821
00:54:22.196 --> 00:54:23.263
[thuds on door]

822
00:54:25.533 --> 00:54:26.667
[thuds on door]

823
00:54:28.536 --> 00:54:30.403
-[creaking]
-[thuds]

824
00:54:30.538 --> 00:54:33.875
-[breath trembling] Children?
-[thuds]

825
00:54:36.409 --> 00:54:38.012
[thudding continues]

826
00:54:54.427 --> 00:54:56.764
[sinister music playing]

827
00:55:14.248 --> 00:55:15.482
[dramatic music spike]

828
00:55:17.618 --> 00:55:20.021
Please open the door.

829
00:55:21.689 --> 00:55:24.625
Did you come back
to return what you stole?

830
00:55:26.127 --> 00:55:26.994
[Thya] Uh...

831
00:55:28.062 --> 00:55:30.463
Oh. Exactly.

832
00:55:38.039 --> 00:55:39.941
[music beat intensifies]

833
00:55:44.745 --> 00:55:45.980
[Polly thuds. screams]

834
00:55:49.584 --> 00:55:53.054
-[Susan] Oh. my God.
Mom. are you okay?
-[Polly groaning]

835
00:55:54.589 --> 00:55:56.023
[Susan] Mom. are you okay?

836
00:55:56.157 --> 00:55:58.059
[eerie music playing]

837
00:55:58.860 --> 00:56:00.761
You're fine.
It's okay. I got you.

838
00:56:01.796 --> 00:56:03.598
You're okay. It's okay.

839
00:56:06.133 --> 00:56:07.568
[squelching]

840
00:56:07.702 --> 00:56:10.738
[Thya in demonic voice]
We will destroy you.

841
00:56:12.540 --> 00:56:15.408
We will destroy you.

842
00:56:19.379 --> 00:56:21.682
No more a wise man.

843
00:56:23.217 --> 00:56:26.554
We will destroy you.

844
00:56:29.123 --> 00:56:31.491
-[both breathing shakily]
-Should I go.

845
00:56:32.660 --> 00:56:34.095
or do you wanna?

846
00:56:36.898 --> 00:56:37.765
You go.

847
00:56:43.237 --> 00:56:44.572
Get Grandma upstairs.

848
00:56:56.183 --> 00:56:57.919
[breath trembling]

849
00:57:10.531 --> 00:57:12.166
[breath trembling]

850
00:57:17.972 --> 00:57:19.439
[creaking]

851
00:57:27.048 --> 00:57:27.949
[mouthing]

852
00:57:42.229 --> 00:57:45.800
You thought I'd let you have
all the men in this family
to yourself?

853
00:57:47.401 --> 00:57:49.170
[both screaming]

854
00:57:53.641 --> 00:57:54.942
Joseph. come!

855
00:58:03.451 --> 00:58:05.019
Help!

856
00:58:05.152 --> 00:58:08.923
Don't bother. babe.
That's not his style.

857
00:58:11.792 --> 00:58:13.127
I said. "Come!"

858
00:58:13.661 --> 00:58:15.162
[both gasp]

859
00:58:16.530 --> 00:58:17.631
Susan.

860
00:58:18.933 --> 00:58:20.868
stop coddling the boy.

861
00:58:23.371 --> 00:58:25.706
He has something that we need.

862
00:58:28.609 --> 00:58:32.046
-[screaming]
-[Joseph] No! No! [grunts]

863
00:58:50.097 --> 00:58:51.032
[both scream]

864
00:58:55.970 --> 00:58:57.905
Give us what we came for!

865
00:58:58.406 --> 00:59:00.641
[beeping]

866
00:59:00.775 --> 00:59:03.644
[clamoring. screaming
downstairs]

867
00:59:03.778 --> 00:59:05.913
I told you she was a thief.

868
00:59:21.862 --> 00:59:24.632
[clicks. knife motor whirring]

869
00:59:30.505 --> 00:59:33.274
[chuckles] Oh. so
you're brave now?

870
00:59:56.030 --> 00:59:56.997
Boo.

871
00:59:58.466 --> 00:59:59.366
[Joseph screams]

872
00:59:59.500 --> 01:00:02.002
[gasping. straining]

873
01:00:04.438 --> 01:00:05.306
[grunts]

874
01:00:09.343 --> 01:00:10.344
[groaning]

875
01:00:22.223 --> 01:00:23.390
I was your first.

876
01:00:24.593 --> 01:00:26.660
I'll make sure I'm your last.

877
01:00:28.229 --> 01:00:29.130
[Joseph screams]

878
01:00:29.598 --> 01:00:32.199
[Thya laughing]

879
01:00:33.667 --> 01:00:34.735
[Joseph grunts]

880
01:00:49.283 --> 01:00:51.418
So you wouldn't
shoot your father.

881
01:00:54.523 --> 01:00:55.656
but killing me...

882
01:01:11.172 --> 01:01:12.106
is easy?

883
01:01:15.843 --> 01:01:17.311
[Thya chuckles]

884
01:01:17.444 --> 01:01:20.214
[Polly] Come here. young lady!
I have what you want!

885
01:01:24.385 --> 01:01:28.222
[Joseph groaning. gasps]

886
01:01:28.355 --> 01:01:29.690
Be right back. baby.

887
01:01:50.177 --> 01:01:52.079
The money is under my mattress.

888
01:01:53.047 --> 01:01:55.382
Take it and leave us alone.

889
01:01:57.451 --> 01:01:58.319
Aww.

890
01:01:59.521 --> 01:02:01.755
It's all broken in here.

891
01:02:03.424 --> 01:02:05.826
But there is something
that we want

892
01:02:05.960 --> 01:02:08.262
in that little head of yours.

893
01:02:10.998 --> 01:02:13.767
Your husband must have told you
where it is.

894
01:02:18.673 --> 01:02:19.740
Huh?

895
01:02:24.579 --> 01:02:26.413
[humming]

896
01:02:29.416 --> 01:02:30.284
Mmm.

897
01:02:43.430 --> 01:02:46.000
Boop. This will fix you.

898
01:02:55.209 --> 01:02:56.076
Polly.

899
01:02:57.044 --> 01:02:58.112
where's your leg?

900
01:03:09.890 --> 01:03:11.892
-Yeah. They don't--
-[grunts]

901
01:03:16.397 --> 01:03:19.933
The Circle
of the Wise Men failed.
Your grandpa failed.

902
01:03:20.535 --> 01:03:21.468
You'll all die tonight.

903
01:03:28.643 --> 01:03:31.746
[Joseph grunting]

904
01:03:31.879 --> 01:03:34.315
[eerie music playing]

905
01:03:39.621 --> 01:03:41.255
[screams]

906
01:03:49.631 --> 01:03:51.932
[sobbing]

907
01:04:05.647 --> 01:04:07.915
[sobbing]

908
01:04:08.048 --> 01:04:10.417
[eerie music continues]

909
01:04:14.589 --> 01:04:17.157
[Will. echoing] <i>Alice.</i>
<i>Alice. Alice.</i>

910
01:04:18.827 --> 01:04:20.861
<i>I'm coming. Alice.</i>

911
01:04:22.697 --> 01:04:23.698
<i>I'm coming for you.</i>

912
01:04:23.832 --> 01:04:25.165
[Alice groaning]

913
01:04:58.666 --> 01:04:59.534
[Alice] Joe.

914
01:05:00.802 --> 01:05:02.202
what's the Circle
of the Wise Men?

915
01:05:03.370 --> 01:05:05.305
I didn't think
that it was real.

916
01:05:05.439 --> 01:05:07.307
Stop hiding stuff
and just tell me.

917
01:05:07.441 --> 01:05:09.410
I saw those fucked up drawings
you threw out.

918
01:05:12.446 --> 01:05:15.182
Did Will ever tell you
about our grandfather?

919
01:05:19.386 --> 01:05:23.257
Growing up. we were always told
he was unstable.

920
01:05:23.390 --> 01:05:25.359
In his journals.
he described it as this group.

921
01:05:25.492 --> 01:05:28.262
Convinced the devil
had been here.

922
01:05:30.063 --> 01:05:33.000
Would return if anyone read
from when he called the...

923
01:05:36.236 --> 01:05:37.471
The <i>Book of the Dead.</i>

924
01:05:46.280 --> 01:05:49.183
My grandfather left his family
to travel the world.

925
01:05:49.316 --> 01:05:52.019
researching
and collecting artifacts

926
01:05:52.152 --> 01:05:54.121
as protection from all this.

927
01:05:54.254 --> 01:05:55.422
[Alice] You still have them?

928
01:05:57.357 --> 01:06:00.327
My mom asked me to throw
everything away after he died.

929
01:06:00.461 --> 01:06:01.563
-but... No. no. no.
-Fuck.

930
01:06:01.696 --> 01:06:02.797
She asked. but I didn't.

931
01:06:03.865 --> 01:06:06.467
There's still some stuff hidden
up in the attic.

932
01:06:07.468 --> 01:06:08.937
And Thya.

933
01:06:09.069 --> 01:06:12.574
that thing inside her said
they were looking
for something.

934
01:06:13.541 --> 01:06:16.343
Maybe whatever that is.
it can stop them.

935
01:06:19.146 --> 01:06:22.149
[fizzing]

936
01:06:22.282 --> 01:06:24.686
Mom. I need you
to drink this. please.

937
01:06:30.658 --> 01:06:32.660
[Polly] Can you look
under the bed?

938
01:06:32.794 --> 01:06:36.196
Daddy always checks
to make sure
there aren't any monsters.

939
01:06:47.842 --> 01:06:48.743
No monsters.

940
01:06:49.443 --> 01:06:50.712
[Polly] You're lying.

941
01:06:54.716 --> 01:06:56.450
Don't worry. [kisses]

942
01:06:56.584 --> 01:06:57.652
you're safe here.

943
01:07:09.229 --> 01:07:10.330
Good night. Mom.

944
01:07:15.235 --> 01:07:16.604
[Polly] Good night. Susan.

945
01:07:20.742 --> 01:07:21.809
What did you call me?

946
01:07:56.410 --> 01:07:58.111
[Polly] Come. sweetheart.

947
01:08:08.923 --> 01:08:09.824
[whimpers]

948
01:08:11.826 --> 01:08:12.694
Mom.

949
01:08:14.227 --> 01:08:15.697
I missed you.

950
01:08:17.665 --> 01:08:21.301
[crying] I missed you so much.

951
01:08:23.738 --> 01:08:25.607
[Polly] We share
the same dream.

952
01:08:26.340 --> 01:08:28.175
It can still come true.

953
01:08:29.443 --> 01:08:32.680
The whole family
can be reunited.

954
01:08:35.282 --> 01:08:37.250
Will's already on his way.

955
01:08:38.185 --> 01:08:40.855
-He'll be here soon.
-[gasps]

956
01:08:48.696 --> 01:08:50.464
[Polly] Don't be scared. Susan.

957
01:08:58.338 --> 01:08:59.907
[knock at window]

958
01:09:01.976 --> 01:09:04.545
[Polly. in demonic voice]
Remember what you said
at the funeral.

959
01:09:05.980 --> 01:09:08.716
That you would give
everything you have

960
01:09:08.850 --> 01:09:12.319
for us all
to be together again.

961
01:09:12.452 --> 01:09:15.222
[Susan sobbing softly]

962
01:09:40.581 --> 01:09:43.518
Without your family.
you're nothing.

963
01:09:47.121 --> 01:09:49.322
[sobbing softly]

964
01:09:52.927 --> 01:09:54.494
I miss you.

965
01:09:56.931 --> 01:09:57.832
I miss us.

966
01:09:57.965 --> 01:09:59.834
[sobbing softly]

967
01:10:34.035 --> 01:10:36.671
[dramatic music playing]

968
01:10:39.006 --> 01:10:40.407
[Susan moans]

969
01:11:16.144 --> 01:11:17.444
[Susan gasps]

970
01:11:26.087 --> 01:11:29.023
You haven't kissed me
like that in years.

971
01:11:45.438 --> 01:11:46.707
Your father's
not there anymore.

972
01:11:46.841 --> 01:11:49.577
-Maybe we could-- [gasps]
-[barking]

973
01:11:51.979 --> 01:11:52.847
[Susan] Joseph.

974
01:11:55.082 --> 01:11:57.752
Hey. is Grandma okay?
Everything good?

975
01:11:57.885 --> 01:11:59.654
Yes. Everything's better now.

976
01:12:02.422 --> 01:12:03.791
I need you to trust me.

977
01:12:05.893 --> 01:12:06.761
Trust you?

978
01:12:07.360 --> 01:12:08.596
They're not our enemies.

979
01:12:09.362 --> 01:12:10.832
I realize that now.

980
01:12:10.965 --> 01:12:13.734
They just want something back
that my father stole.

981
01:12:13.868 --> 01:12:16.469
I told you he was a bad man.

982
01:12:17.205 --> 01:12:18.105
It's simple.

983
01:12:18.739 --> 01:12:19.941
Tell them where it is.

984
01:12:20.074 --> 01:12:22.810
Give them what they want.
and this ends.

985
01:12:24.477 --> 01:12:25.780
We can be happy again.

986
01:12:27.181 --> 01:12:28.448
Where... What is...

987
01:12:30.417 --> 01:12:31.552
Our weapon.

988
01:12:34.121 --> 01:12:35.990
We threw everything away.

989
01:12:36.123 --> 01:12:37.024
You're lying to me.

990
01:12:38.659 --> 01:12:39.927
Tell us where it is.

991
01:12:41.562 --> 01:12:42.830
"Us"?

992
01:12:42.964 --> 01:12:44.532
Where is the Kandarian dagger?

993
01:12:44.665 --> 01:12:45.933
[bulbs shattering]

994
01:12:47.602 --> 01:12:50.605
[all screaming]

995
01:12:50.738 --> 01:12:53.274
[clamoring. screaming
continues]

996
01:12:53.406 --> 01:12:54.842
[Joseph] Alice...

997
01:12:58.079 --> 01:12:58.980
[Susan] Leave him alone!

998
01:12:59.113 --> 01:13:01.616
[Alice running.
sobbing. panting]

999
01:13:05.052 --> 01:13:06.520
[glass breaks]

1000
01:13:06.654 --> 01:13:09.790
You need to stop meddling
in our family affairs.

1001
01:13:10.324 --> 01:13:11.726
[Susan sobbing]

1002
01:13:12.360 --> 01:13:13.794
You promised!

1003
01:13:14.729 --> 01:13:16.664
You promised not to hurt him!

1004
01:13:21.302 --> 01:13:22.904
[snarling]

1005
01:13:25.940 --> 01:13:29.010
Finally some use
for this revolting
piece of shit.

1006
01:13:29.143 --> 01:13:30.410
[Susan screams]

1007
01:13:31.145 --> 01:13:32.780
[Joseph straining]

1008
01:13:34.081 --> 01:13:35.016
[Edgar] Come.

1009
01:13:36.684 --> 01:13:37.818
See what you did.

1010
01:13:39.320 --> 01:13:41.756
[groaning]

1011
01:13:42.857 --> 01:13:44.091
[Joseph whimpering]

1012
01:13:47.895 --> 01:13:50.598
Finally. something
you can be proud of.

1013
01:13:50.731 --> 01:13:52.767
[screams. muffled scream]

1014
01:13:53.668 --> 01:13:55.670
[groaning]

1015
01:13:58.606 --> 01:13:59.740
[muffled] The dagger!

1016
01:14:00.207 --> 01:14:01.208
[groans. spits]

1017
01:14:01.342 --> 01:14:02.610
Did you say something?

1018
01:14:02.743 --> 01:14:04.444
I know where the dagger is!

1019
01:14:08.249 --> 01:14:11.285
Nothing will stand
in our way now.

1020
01:14:11.419 --> 01:14:12.887
once we have the dag--

1021
01:14:14.655 --> 01:14:16.057
[both groaning]

1022
01:14:23.197 --> 01:14:24.932
[both groaning. grunting]

1023
01:14:27.401 --> 01:14:28.468
[Joseph] No!

1024
01:14:29.570 --> 01:14:30.938
-[objects clattering]
-[Edgar] Ah!

1025
01:14:31.072 --> 01:14:33.107
-[Susan] Get off him!
-[Joseph] Mom. Oh!

1026
01:14:34.508 --> 01:14:35.776
[Susan] Get off him!

1027
01:14:35.910 --> 01:14:38.813
-Edgar! Get off!
-Oh. fuck.

1028
01:14:39.413 --> 01:14:40.681
[Joseph screams]

1029
01:14:42.049 --> 01:14:43.584
[whimpering]

1030
01:14:45.586 --> 01:14:47.121
[Susan screams]

1031
01:14:50.291 --> 01:14:51.726
[Susan] Stop!

1032
01:14:51.859 --> 01:14:54.295
-[Alice whimpering]
-[Susan] Stop! Stop it! Stop!

1033
01:14:54.428 --> 01:14:56.430
[thumping]

1034
01:14:56.564 --> 01:14:59.800
[Susan screaming]
Help me! Help me!

1035
01:15:04.238 --> 01:15:06.107
[Edgar yells]

1036
01:15:10.978 --> 01:15:13.381
-[screams]
-[Susan] No. no! No!

1037
01:15:13.514 --> 01:15:15.950
-[screams]
-[Susan] No!

1038
01:15:23.624 --> 01:15:24.658
[Susan] Get off me!

1039
01:15:25.192 --> 01:15:26.060
[Susan] Get off!

1040
01:15:27.995 --> 01:15:30.197
-[Edgar snarls]
-[muffled sobbing]

1041
01:15:33.100 --> 01:15:34.668
-[objects clattering]
-[Joseph] No!

1042
01:15:35.469 --> 01:15:37.571
-No!
-[Edgar grunts]

1043
01:15:38.706 --> 01:15:39.774
Argh!

1044
01:15:49.784 --> 01:15:50.851
[Joseph] No!

1045
01:15:51.318 --> 01:15:53.154
[Alice sobbing]

1046
01:15:53.287 --> 01:15:56.791
-[Edgar. Joseph grunting]
-[Joseph] No! No!

1047
01:15:59.293 --> 01:16:01.896
-[grunting continues]
-[objects clattering]

1048
01:16:07.168 --> 01:16:08.702
-[door cracking]
-[muffled scream]

1049
01:16:08.836 --> 01:16:10.004
[Edgar] Where's the dagger?

1050
01:16:11.405 --> 01:16:12.339
Where is it?

1051
01:16:14.208 --> 01:16:15.209
Answer me!

1052
01:16:16.210 --> 01:16:17.244
Answer me!

1053
01:16:20.114 --> 01:16:22.249
[Joseph] Find it. Before them.

1054
01:16:23.117 --> 01:16:24.618
[screams]

1055
01:16:24.752 --> 01:16:26.954
-[receding footsteps]
-[Joseph] No!

1056
01:16:28.689 --> 01:16:30.257
[objects clattering]

1057
01:16:31.425 --> 01:16:32.660
[Joseph screams]

1058
01:16:34.929 --> 01:16:36.730
[footsteps going upstairs]

1059
01:16:40.668 --> 01:16:43.871
[footsteps thumping]

1060
01:16:49.643 --> 01:16:50.845
[door creaks]

1061
01:16:58.652 --> 01:17:00.988
[breath trembling]

1062
01:17:03.457 --> 01:17:04.325
No.

1063
01:17:10.331 --> 01:17:13.701
[breathing heavily]

1064
01:17:21.242 --> 01:17:24.111
-[motor revving]
-[whirring]

1065
01:17:34.488 --> 01:17:36.090
[dog barking]

1066
01:17:56.410 --> 01:17:57.711
[breath trembling]

1067
01:18:06.588 --> 01:18:07.788
[sobs]

1068
01:18:11.959 --> 01:18:13.127
[glass breaks]

1069
01:18:35.816 --> 01:18:36.884
[Polly snarls]

1070
01:18:37.017 --> 01:18:38.986
[Alice groaning]

1071
01:18:48.597 --> 01:18:50.164
Oh. stop.

1072
01:18:50.297 --> 01:18:53.067
I'm just giving you
what you want.

1073
01:18:53.200 --> 01:18:55.169
I know you liked it
when Will hurt you.

1074
01:18:55.803 --> 01:18:57.471
Isn't that why you stayed?

1075
01:18:59.340 --> 01:19:00.941
[Alice panting]

1076
01:19:03.444 --> 01:19:04.478
Ah!

1077
01:19:04.613 --> 01:19:06.280
Don't turn a deaf ear.

1078
01:19:07.081 --> 01:19:08.717
I asked you a question.

1079
01:19:08.849 --> 01:19:10.818
[panting]

1080
01:19:13.487 --> 01:19:14.922
[Alice sobbing]

1081
01:19:19.860 --> 01:19:21.428
[Alice whimpering]

1082
01:19:23.665 --> 01:19:26.534
[groaning. screaming]

1083
01:19:26.668 --> 01:19:27.535
[sound muffled]

1084
01:19:29.403 --> 01:19:30.504
Susan.

1085
01:19:30.639 --> 01:19:31.805
Help.

1086
01:19:32.641 --> 01:19:33.575
[Polly] Susan. dear.

1087
01:19:34.542 --> 01:19:36.143
would you mind
pushing the throttle

1088
01:19:36.277 --> 01:19:39.046
to tear
this bitch's face off. please?

1089
01:19:39.179 --> 01:19:41.282
She brought chaos
into this family.

1090
01:19:42.049 --> 01:19:44.351
Your son died because of her.

1091
01:19:45.953 --> 01:19:47.254
Do it.

1092
01:19:47.756 --> 01:19:48.856
For Will.

1093
01:19:53.595 --> 01:19:54.495
Do it.

1094
01:19:58.265 --> 01:19:59.433
Do it!

1095
01:20:03.504 --> 01:20:04.838
Oh. Susan!

1096
01:20:05.640 --> 01:20:06.940
Do it.

1097
01:20:07.841 --> 01:20:09.276
I'm sorry. Alice.

1098
01:20:11.445 --> 01:20:12.547
[screams]

1099
01:20:19.086 --> 01:20:20.154
[demonic growl]

1100
01:20:21.488 --> 01:20:23.891
-[chair beeps]
-[whimpering]

1101
01:20:24.024 --> 01:20:26.093
[beeping]

1102
01:20:41.942 --> 01:20:43.410
[sobbing softly]

1103
01:20:56.023 --> 01:20:57.958
[squelching]

1104
01:20:58.092 --> 01:20:59.828
[muffled groan]

1105
01:21:01.730 --> 01:21:03.397
-[gasps]
-[ear ringing]

1106
01:21:36.531 --> 01:21:37.599
[Joseph screams]

1107
01:21:44.572 --> 01:21:45.607
Is it Joseph?

1108
01:21:47.474 --> 01:21:48.475
Is it my son?

1109
01:21:56.751 --> 01:21:58.285
[whimpers] No.

1110
01:21:59.654 --> 01:22:01.488
[whimpering]

1111
01:22:03.625 --> 01:22:05.058
[in French]

1112
01:22:12.299 --> 01:22:14.569
-[snarling]
-[whimpers]

1113
01:22:16.003 --> 01:22:18.172
-[hammering at door]
-[Alice grunts]

1114
01:22:22.577 --> 01:22:25.245
-[sizzling]
-[Susan cries out]

1115
01:22:29.049 --> 01:22:30.050
[in English]
What are you doing?

1116
01:22:30.184 --> 01:22:31.485
[in French]

1117
01:22:31.619 --> 01:22:32.787
[in English]
You should be grateful

1118
01:22:32.921 --> 01:22:34.154
I didn't leave you back there.

1119
01:22:34.689 --> 01:22:36.558
Don't you dare move.

1120
01:22:38.959 --> 01:22:40.327
Grateful?

1121
01:22:44.699 --> 01:22:46.066
[moans]

1122
01:22:46.200 --> 01:22:48.068
My family is gone.

1123
01:22:48.937 --> 01:22:51.205
Everyone I love is gone

1124
01:22:51.338 --> 01:22:53.207
because of you.

1125
01:22:54.441 --> 01:22:57.444
All you've ever done
is bring us pain.

1126
01:22:58.445 --> 01:22:59.714
[groans]

1127
01:23:02.717 --> 01:23:03.685
[winces]

1128
01:23:03.818 --> 01:23:04.886
I hate you.

1129
01:23:05.018 --> 01:23:06.888
Oh. shut up. Susan!

1130
01:23:07.020 --> 01:23:08.989
Shut the fuck up!

1131
01:23:09.122 --> 01:23:11.325
I didn't bring anything
to your family.

1132
01:23:11.458 --> 01:23:13.327
It was already there.

1133
01:23:14.194 --> 01:23:15.730
You see this?

1134
01:23:16.831 --> 01:23:18.131
You see. Susan?

1135
01:23:18.265 --> 01:23:19.366
This is your son.

1136
01:23:19.500 --> 01:23:21.134
This is what he was capable of.

1137
01:23:21.268 --> 01:23:23.638
-It was an accident.
-No. it wasn't!

1138
01:23:25.874 --> 01:23:28.510
It was not and you knew.

1139
01:23:29.644 --> 01:23:31.345
You knew. Susan.

1140
01:23:32.647 --> 01:23:36.049
You deserve everything
that's happened to you.

1141
01:23:37.284 --> 01:23:40.555
Every fucking thing.
But you know what?

1142
01:23:42.122 --> 01:23:43.423
It's behind me now.

1143
01:23:44.224 --> 01:23:46.193
I don't give a shit anymore.

1144
01:23:47.261 --> 01:23:49.263
[electric saw whirring]

1145
01:23:55.837 --> 01:23:56.905
[Susan] You're right.

1146
01:23:57.437 --> 01:24:00.073
Your past is behind you.

1147
01:24:01.976 --> 01:24:04.746
Right... Right behind you.

1148
01:24:06.280 --> 01:24:08.048
Like a shadow.

1149
01:24:09.684 --> 01:24:11.318
Can't escape it.

1150
01:24:12.386 --> 01:24:15.122
Just when you think
you're safe.

1151
01:24:16.089 --> 01:24:17.157
Healed.

1152
01:24:18.225 --> 01:24:21.796
When you breathe
a quivering sigh...

1153
01:24:23.463 --> 01:24:26.266
my son will be there.

1154
01:24:27.802 --> 01:24:29.503
As a husband should.

1155
01:24:31.471 --> 01:24:36.844
And he will burn you down...

1156
01:24:37.912 --> 01:24:41.481
like the whore you are.

1157
01:24:44.586 --> 01:24:46.888
[in demonic voice]
You will be dead by dawn!

1158
01:24:47.021 --> 01:24:48.623
[grunts]

1159
01:24:56.064 --> 01:24:57.464
[both grunting]

1160
01:25:04.572 --> 01:25:05.773
-[Susan snarls]
-[Alice screams]

1161
01:25:22.857 --> 01:25:24.191
[growling]

1162
01:25:24.993 --> 01:25:26.159
[yells]

1163
01:25:34.869 --> 01:25:36.403
[gasping]

1164
01:25:47.715 --> 01:25:49.182
[blade whirring]

1165
01:25:51.786 --> 01:25:53.387
[screams]

1166
01:25:59.927 --> 01:26:01.328
[Susan screams in agony]

1167
01:26:15.076 --> 01:26:16.678
[panting]

1168
01:26:39.000 --> 01:26:40.333
[Joseph] Alice.

1169
01:26:40.467 --> 01:26:41.903
Help me up.

1170
01:26:42.036 --> 01:26:44.471
I know where the dagger is.
I'll help you find it.

1171
01:26:46.641 --> 01:26:48.241
[in demonic voice] And then
I'll cut you open with it

1172
01:26:48.375 --> 01:26:50.044
like my brother should have.

1173
01:26:50.945 --> 01:26:53.915
You're worthless.
Just like my grandfather.

1174
01:26:54.048 --> 01:26:55.783
Shut up!

1175
01:26:55.917 --> 01:26:58.886
He never found it.
and you never will.

1176
01:27:00.722 --> 01:27:03.356
Let me end your miserable life.

1177
01:27:03.490 --> 01:27:05.993
You like pain. anyway.

1178
01:27:06.127 --> 01:27:07.795
[gasps. whimpers]

1179
01:27:09.664 --> 01:27:12.365
That's why you let Will
hurt you. Isn't it?

1180
01:27:12.867 --> 01:27:15.770
Poor little Alice.

1181
01:27:20.440 --> 01:27:23.644
You'll be found
in an attic alone.

1182
01:27:25.245 --> 01:27:27.380
Gutted from tit to tail.

1183
01:27:29.382 --> 01:27:31.351
You never wanted kids. anyway.

1184
01:27:32.252 --> 01:27:33.554
Your body is useless.

1185
01:27:34.822 --> 01:27:35.690
[groans]

1186
01:27:35.823 --> 01:27:37.825
[chokes]

1187
01:27:41.195 --> 01:27:43.731
[gasping for air]

1188
01:27:51.271 --> 01:27:52.540
Wrong one.

1189
01:27:55.910 --> 01:27:58.746
The Circle of the Wise Men
is dead.

1190
01:28:02.083 --> 01:28:03.751
[Alice grunts]

1191
01:28:08.355 --> 01:28:09.957
Come here. you little bitch.

1192
01:28:10.591 --> 01:28:12.193
I told you it's not here.

1193
01:28:12.325 --> 01:28:13.895
[both grunt]

1194
01:28:33.614 --> 01:28:35.750
[clattering]

1195
01:28:46.994 --> 01:28:48.930
[breath trembling]

1196
01:29:02.910 --> 01:29:03.778
[shrieks]

1197
01:29:05.246 --> 01:29:06.681
[Alice whimpers]

1198
01:29:15.355 --> 01:29:16.958
[grunting]

1199
01:29:19.126 --> 01:29:20.493
[screams]

1200
01:29:24.665 --> 01:29:26.366
[whimpering]

1201
01:29:32.006 --> 01:29:33.608
[snarls]

1202
01:29:35.843 --> 01:29:37.477
[snarls]

1203
01:29:42.717 --> 01:29:44.752
[hyperventilating]

1204
01:29:46.087 --> 01:29:47.755
[Susan shrieks]

1205
01:29:49.924 --> 01:29:51.759
[shrieking]

1206
01:29:54.195 --> 01:29:55.730
[electricity sizzling]

1207
01:29:58.165 --> 01:29:59.934
[straining]

1208
01:30:01.335 --> 01:30:03.604
[blade whirring]

1209
01:30:24.558 --> 01:30:25.993
My family will...

1210
01:30:26.127 --> 01:30:27.061
Fuck your family!

1211
01:30:27.194 --> 01:30:28.629
[Edgar groans]

1212
01:30:35.069 --> 01:30:36.904
[blade whirring]

1213
01:30:41.474 --> 01:30:42.777
[whistles]

1214
01:30:46.547 --> 01:30:48.983
[ <i>Elle Etait Si Jolie</i>
by Alain Barriere playing]

1215
01:31:44.238 --> 01:31:45.573
[song ends]

1216
01:31:47.274 --> 01:31:49.643
[Alice whimpering]

1217
01:31:49.777 --> 01:31:51.078
[Will in demonic voice]
Did you stay

1218
01:31:51.212 --> 01:31:52.813
because you liked it?

1219
01:31:52.947 --> 01:31:55.549
Or you were too much
of a coward to leave me?

1220
01:31:55.683 --> 01:31:58.019
[breath trembling]

1221
01:32:01.122 --> 01:32:02.890
Look at you now.

1222
01:32:04.525 --> 01:32:06.894
You still can't leave.

1223
01:32:09.697 --> 01:32:11.832
[wind howling]

1224
01:32:16.670 --> 01:32:19.306
Remember the last thing
you said to me?

1225
01:32:23.644 --> 01:32:25.546
"Go to hell."

1226
01:32:27.882 --> 01:32:29.717
You got your wish.

1227
01:32:34.688 --> 01:32:36.957
[whimpering]

1228
01:32:42.229 --> 01:32:44.899
I shouldn't have hurt you.
Alice.

1229
01:32:45.032 --> 01:32:46.467
I should have killed you.

1230
01:32:46.600 --> 01:32:48.803
[demonic music playing]

1231
01:33:04.251 --> 01:33:06.954
This is where I promised
I'd always be with you.

1232
01:33:09.490 --> 01:33:11.692
[demonic music playing]

1233
01:33:26.073 --> 01:33:29.677
Where I promised that not even
death would do us part.

1234
01:33:32.046 --> 01:33:35.049
I will keep my promise. Alice.

1235
01:33:41.556 --> 01:33:43.023
'Cause without me...

1236
01:33:44.859 --> 01:33:46.994
you are nothing.

1237
01:33:47.862 --> 01:33:49.864
[whimpering]

1238
01:34:05.446 --> 01:34:07.214
[panting]

1239
01:34:14.922 --> 01:34:17.124
[hyperventilating]

1240
01:34:25.032 --> 01:34:26.267
[groans in frustration]

1241
01:34:30.771 --> 01:34:32.206
[hyperventilating]

1242
01:34:33.575 --> 01:34:35.176
[gasps]

1243
01:34:37.478 --> 01:34:39.346
[grunting]

1244
01:34:43.918 --> 01:34:46.120
[suspenseful music playing]

1245
01:34:55.429 --> 01:34:57.698
[hyperventilating]

1246
01:34:57.831 --> 01:34:58.899
Hello?

1247
01:34:59.700 --> 01:35:01.335
[static whine]

1248
01:35:01.468 --> 01:35:02.970
Hello? Hello...

1249
01:35:03.103 --> 01:35:05.139
[ <i>La Chanson Des Vieux Amants</i>
by Jacques Brel playing]

1250
01:35:28.429 --> 01:35:29.531
[Will grunting]

1251
01:35:29.664 --> 01:35:31.065
[music stops]

1252
01:35:32.466 --> 01:35:34.401
[breath trembling]

1253
01:35:39.807 --> 01:35:41.141
[gasps]

1254
01:35:43.444 --> 01:35:44.912
[cries out]

1255
01:35:45.279 --> 01:35:47.114
[screams]

1256
01:35:48.650 --> 01:35:50.017
[gasping]

1257
01:35:59.527 --> 01:36:01.495
[groans]

1258
01:36:01.630 --> 01:36:02.930
[sobs]

1259
01:36:03.063 --> 01:36:05.032
[demonic music playing]

1260
01:36:09.403 --> 01:36:11.205
[Alice wails]

1261
01:36:17.211 --> 01:36:21.716
I could never
have lived without you. Alice.

1262
01:36:22.483 --> 01:36:24.885
I won't let you live
without me.

1263
01:36:30.090 --> 01:36:32.026
[Alice sobbing]

1264
01:36:41.502 --> 01:36:43.237
[sobs]

1265
01:36:46.240 --> 01:36:48.075
[winces]

1266
01:36:50.578 --> 01:36:52.413
[groans]

1267
01:36:56.551 --> 01:36:58.218
[sobbing]

1268
01:37:03.991 --> 01:37:05.492
[Will] Shit.

1269
01:37:06.060 --> 01:37:07.961
[Alice grunts]

1270
01:37:08.763 --> 01:37:10.264
[Will] Where is the dagger?

1271
01:37:13.067 --> 01:37:15.436
-Where is it?
-[crying]

1272
01:37:16.870 --> 01:37:18.339
Where is it. Alice?

1273
01:37:21.543 --> 01:37:23.077
Go get it.

1274
01:37:24.445 --> 01:37:26.113
[grunting]

1275
01:37:28.015 --> 01:37:29.283
[cries out]

1276
01:37:29.416 --> 01:37:30.384
[grunts]

1277
01:37:37.792 --> 01:37:39.460
[panting]

1278
01:37:44.465 --> 01:37:45.899
[grunts]

1279
01:37:49.604 --> 01:37:51.105
[yells]

1280
01:37:51.639 --> 01:37:53.107
[Will grunting]

1281
01:37:56.076 --> 01:37:57.344
[roars]

1282
01:38:02.584 --> 01:38:04.318
[grunting]

1283
01:38:07.020 --> 01:38:09.423
[Will screaming]

1284
01:38:16.897 --> 01:38:18.432
[Alice gasps]

1285
01:38:30.845 --> 01:38:32.580
[splutters]

1286
01:38:38.051 --> 01:38:39.621
[screams]

1287
01:38:39.754 --> 01:38:41.355
[continues screaming]

1288
01:38:41.890 --> 01:38:43.323
Where is the dagger?

1289
01:38:43.892 --> 01:38:45.492
Speak or burn. bitch!

1290
01:38:46.895 --> 01:38:49.296
Here's your fucking dagger!

1291
01:38:58.972 --> 01:39:00.642
[exhales]

1292
01:39:06.246 --> 01:39:08.382
[breath trembling]

1293
01:39:11.485 --> 01:39:13.454
[in normal voice] I love you.

1294
01:39:32.005 --> 01:39:34.141
[Alice sighs]

1295
01:39:41.448 --> 01:39:43.283
[sobs]

1296
01:39:44.318 --> 01:39:46.286
That is not enough.

1297
01:39:51.926 --> 01:39:53.728
[squelching]

1298
01:40:00.067 --> 01:40:02.069
[sizzling]

1299
01:40:02.804 --> 01:40:05.005
[gasping]

1300
01:40:05.138 --> 01:40:07.509
[demonic music playing]

1301
01:40:19.654 --> 01:40:21.656
[panting]

1302
01:40:36.069 --> 01:40:38.338
[strains. grunts]

1303
01:40:50.284 --> 01:40:52.820
[distant sirens approaching]

1304
01:41:01.261 --> 01:41:03.363
[sobs]

1305
01:41:09.771 --> 01:41:11.739
[continues sobbing]

1306
01:41:20.682 --> 01:41:23.585
[woman on radio] <i>...Primary.</i>
<i>five. five. seven. four.</i>

1307
01:41:32.292 --> 01:41:33.861
Got a cigarette?

1308
01:41:35.563 --> 01:41:38.265
-I'm not really allowed to--
-Just give it to me.

1309
01:41:47.542 --> 01:41:48.810
Who did this to you?

1310
01:41:56.084 --> 01:41:57.685
My ex-husband.

1311
01:42:03.591 --> 01:42:06.126
[melancholy music playing]

1312
01:42:37.025 --> 01:42:39.259
[French rap song playing]

1313
01:44:19.160 --> 01:44:20.695
[song ends]

1314
01:44:25.666 --> 01:44:27.668
[ominous music playing]

1315
01:44:33.875 --> 01:44:35.576
[grunts]

1316
01:44:37.945 --> 01:44:40.648
[in English]
Wicked little French bitch.

1317
01:44:50.825 --> 01:44:53.561
Ma'am! What happened?
Are you okay?

1318
01:44:53.694 --> 01:44:57.430
[in plaintive voice] Oh!
Thank Heaven! Please help me!

1319
01:44:57.565 --> 01:44:59.567
She stole my legs!

1320
01:45:01.202 --> 01:45:03.838
[in demonic voice]
But yours will do just fine.

1321
01:45:04.471 --> 01:45:06.406
[snarls]

1322
01:45:07.775 --> 01:45:09.877
[demonic music playing]

1323
01:48:12.593 --> 01:48:14.562
[rattling]

1324
01:48:14.695 --> 01:48:16.130
Yes. sweetie. I know.

1325
01:48:16.263 --> 01:48:18.899
It's no fun coming into work
with me on a Saturday.

1326
01:48:19.033 --> 01:48:21.202
But I've had to do everything
by myself since...

1327
01:48:22.470 --> 01:48:23.471
Well. you know. Mm-hm.

1328
01:48:23.604 --> 01:48:25.139
I'll make it up to you tonight.

1329
01:48:26.240 --> 01:48:28.309
How come you're keeping
all these urns

1330
01:48:28.442 --> 01:48:30.111
for dead people?

1331
01:48:30.244 --> 01:48:31.612
Uh...

1332
01:48:31.746 --> 01:48:32.680
Well...

1333
01:48:32.813 --> 01:48:34.749
[sighs. tuts]

1334
01:48:34.882 --> 01:48:36.417
It's sad. actually.

1335
01:48:36.550 --> 01:48:39.153
These are the people whose
families never came for them.

1336
01:48:39.286 --> 01:48:40.955
So. we keep them here
for a few months

1337
01:48:41.088 --> 01:48:43.124
in case a family member
remembers

1338
01:48:43.257 --> 01:48:44.592
to pick them up one day.

1339
01:48:44.725 --> 01:48:46.093
[bell sounds]

1340
01:48:46.227 --> 01:48:47.928
Okay.
Don't touch anything. okay?

1341
01:48:48.062 --> 01:48:49.430
That might be
about the cremator job.

1342
01:48:49.563 --> 01:48:51.032
I'll be right back.

1343
01:48:57.772 --> 01:48:59.807
"Christopher Leroy."

1344
01:49:02.343 --> 01:49:04.311
"Ellie Bixler."

1345
01:49:06.013 --> 01:49:08.549
-[Ellie] Hey.
-[urn clattering]

1346
01:49:21.095 --> 01:49:22.963
Mom?

1347
01:49:23.097 --> 01:49:24.999
[Ellie] Don't be scared. baby.

1348
01:49:43.417 --> 01:49:45.953
[electricity crackling]

1349
01:49:49.790 --> 01:49:51.792
[dramatic musical sting]

1350
01:49:58.365 --> 01:49:59.967
[snarls]

1351
01:50:07.608 --> 01:50:09.276
[in demonic voice]
Mommy's back.
